                            <comment id="12718778" author="cziegeler" created="Fri, 12 Jun 2009 10:17:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I just committed a fix for this problem; please check and close this bug.&lt;br/&gt;
Thanks&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12718792" author="fmeschbe" created="Fri, 12 Jun 2009 11:03:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for this quick fix.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I just noticed, thata accroding to the MetaType spec, the pid attribute is required. Will just fix it.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12718794" author="fmeschbe" created="Fri, 12 Jun 2009 11:07:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fix the description to be spec compliant.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12718797" author="fmeschbe" created="Fri, 12 Jun 2009 11:13:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;With applying the patch in Rev. 784071 this issue is really solved.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12736086" author="cziegeler" created="Tue, 28 Jul 2009 14:27:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Reopening as the handling of the Designate@factoryPID attribute is wrong: it should only be set if this is not a component factory. Therefore we need a new scr attribute setMetatypeFactoryPID which can be used to optionally set the Designate@factoryPID&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12736090" author="cziegeler" created="Tue, 28 Jul 2009 14:43:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;added a new attribute in revision: 798540. The attribute defaults to false and should only be used with non factory components.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
